  <h2>My jollof rice recipe</h2>
  <p>Hi everyone my name is <strong><em>Collins ifeanyi</em></strong>, Am going to teach you how to cook my favourite food,
    which is jollof rice.
  </p>
  <p>Fist am going list out few ingredient for this delicious meal.</p>
  <p>Second am going to put you through the process of prepairing the 
	jollof rice in steps.</p>
  <!-- unordered list of my ingredient -->
  <P><strong>Ingredient</strong></p>  
  <ul>
    <li>Rice</li>
	<li>Tomatos</li>
	  <ul>
	    <li>fresh tomatos, to be chop or slice in small pieces</li>
	  </ul>
	<li>Dry Fish</li>
	<li>Onion</li>
	<li>Ginger and Garlic</li>
	  <ul>
	    <li>Dried ginger is the perfect choice far me, the garlic could be fresh</li>
	  </ul>
	<li>Fresh Perper</li>
	<li>Salt</li>
	<li>Vegetable Oil or Olive Oil</li>
	<li>Carrot</li>
	<li>Green Perper</li>
	<li>Meat</li>
	<li>Seasoning</li>
	<li>Special jollof rice spices</li>
  </ul>
  <!-- ordered list of prepairing -->
  <p><strong>Preparation</strong></P>
  <ol>
   <li>First you put a clean pot in the gass and add two litter of clean water , and allow to boil.</li>
	 <ul>
	   <li>ie, the amount of water to be added will depend on the quantity of rice you are cooking.</li>
	   <li>add the already washed rice into the boiling water and allow to boil for five minutes</li>
	   <ul>
		 <li>then put the pot down from the gass, put out the water, wash again then cover for later.</li>
		 </ul>
	 </ul>	
   <li>Secondly, you chop the meat in sizeable form wash with water and salt.</li>
     <ul>
	   <li>after washing, you pre-boil the meat, add some spices, salt and boil for 15 to 20 minutes, after which you put the pot down for later.</li>
     </ul>
   <li>Now you have to pre-fry the tomatos and the onion</li>
     <ul>
       <li>after you most have fry the tomatos for about 5 to 10 minutes, you now add the pre-boild meat and it source, you add the chop carrot, green perper</li>
	   <li>you add the ginger and garlic,seasoning and the special jollof rice spices and allow to boil for 3 to 4 minutes then you add the already pre-boild rice</li>
	 </ul>  
  </ol>
